obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_888  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper characterizes the localization of Calcium /Calmodulin kinase II beta and alpha in isolated post-synaptic density fractions.\n\nFigure 8 presents a quantification of the immunogold labeling as a function of age. Substantial labeling densities are present for both isoforms.\n\nTable 2 presents the summary of the immunogold labeling quantifications.\n\nFigure 1 presents the antibodies used. For all experiments, a negative control was made in the absence of primary antibody. The small amount of non-specific labeling was quantified and subtracted as background.\n\nFigure S1 presents western blots for each of the antibodies. A single band is seen for the CaMKII alpha and beta, however, the blots are cropped so specificity evaluation is difficult.\n\n19/8/2017 Pim\n- The isolated also contain NMDAR subunits so in ference to the cytoplasmic part of the PSD is not valid.. Experimental description: Subcellular fractions enriched in postsynaptic densities were obtained from rat brains by using a slightly modified version of the protocol developed by Cohen et al. (1977)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_888" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

